FBIS4-45317 "jptdd025__l94069" JPRS-TDD-94-025-L JPRS Narcotics 3 June 1994 NEAR EAST & SOUTH ASIA LEBANON One Arrested, 2,250 Grams of Cocaine Seized at Beirut Airport One Arrested, 2,250 Grams of Cocaine Seized at Beirut Airport NC0306190794 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1115 GMT 3 Jun 94 NC0306190794 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] This morning customs officials at Beirut airport foiled an attempt to smuggle a quantity of drugs into Lebanon. Husayn 'Ali al-Sahili, born in 1973 in Kafr Zabad in al-Biqa', was arrested upon his arrival from Colombia via Amsterdam, and 2,250 grams of cocaine were seized with him. The drugs were hidden in an innovative and technical way--inside a case with a false bottom and inside two nylon envelopes. The case passed, undetected, through X-ray machines in European airports. Al-Sahili was arrested and referred to the counternarcotics office. The local value of the seized drug was estimated at $70,000 and estimated at $5,000 in Colombia.
